==English==

===Noun phrase===
'''[[Mexican]] [[overdrive]]'''
# ''(US slang, based on a stereotype)'' The neutral gear when used while a vehicle is moving, especially when it is used to save fuel or to coast down hill faster than a vehicle can go in gear.  (This is illegal in some places.)
#:''He shifted his car out of gear, at the top of the hill, and coasted down in '''Mexican overdrive'''.''

